---
import Icon from './Icon.astro';

const myths = [
  {
    myth: "ChatGPT killed SEO",
    truth: "ChatGPT has 0.25% of Google's search volume. 95% of Americans still use Google monthly. SEO captures 99.75% of search traffic.",
    iconName: "cpu"
  },
  {
    myth: "AI Overviews ruined organic traffic",
    truth: "June 2025 update: Zero-click increased from 56% to 69% on news, but commercial queries still drive clicks. Adapt, don't abandon.",
    iconName: "chart-growth"
  },
  {
    myth: "Just use programmatic SEO like everyone",
    truth: "Zapier: 50K pages, 5.8M sessions/month. But 95% of programmatic attempts fail. Success requires strategy, not just scale.",
    iconName: "puzzle"
  },
  {
    myth: "Google's algorithm is unpredictable",
    truth: "2025 focus: E-E-A-T, Core Web Vitals, topical authority. Winners have clear strategies (80% success) vs guessing (37%).",
    iconName: "cog"
  }
];
---

<section class="section py-32 bg-gradient-section relative overflow-hidden">
  <div class="container relative z-10">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 animate-fade-in">
        The <span class="text-accent">Uncomfortable Truth</span> About SEO
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-3xl mx-auto animate-fade-in" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">
        September 2025 reality check: While everyone panics about AI, smart companies are quietly dominating search.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      {myths.map((item, index) => (
        <div class="animate-fade-in" style={`animation-delay: ${index * 0.1}s`}>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 group">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary to-primary-darker rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <Icon name={item.iconName} class="text-white" size="md" />
              </div>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-red-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                    <Icon name="shield-x" class="text-red-600" size="sm" />
                  </div>
                  Myth: {item.myth}
                </h3>
                <p class="text-lg text-primary font-semibold flex items-start gap-2">
                  <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-green-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                    <Icon name="check" class="text-green-600" size="sm" />
                  </div>
                  <span>{item.truth}</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    
    <div class="mt-16 text-center">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-xl max-w-4xl mx-auto animate-fade-in" style="animation-delay: 0.5s">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-primary">The Bottom Line</h3>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-8">
          While competitors chase ChatGPT's 0.25% market share, I'll help you capture the 99.75% still on Google—
          plus prepare for what's next. June's algorithm update proved one thing: strategy beats tactics.
        </p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-xl premium-glow">
          Get a Strategy That Actually Works
          <span class="ml-2">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Background Pattern -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-5"></div>
</section>